main_data.contactSpecialInstructions:
Please ensure you have your MCIS ID badge. If you require one, send a head shot of yourself with the subject line "MCIS ID badge" to info@mcis.on.ca.

Dear interpreter, MCIS shares your telephone number with the SP and if the assignment is for scheduled telephone, there is a likelihood that the SP will call you directly. Please note that they may use private, No caller ID when calling. Please make sure to pick it up.

· If you are able to connect the 3 way call for the SP kindly do so.

· If you are unable to connect or establish a 3 way call, please advise the SP to hang up and call MCIS and they will connect all parties.
main_data.customerNotes:
Mileage is NOT Billable but is payable (out of pocket) for the following laguages: Arabic, Spanish, Mandarin, Nepali, Vietnamese, Farsi, Korean, French, Khmer, Kurdish Sorani, and Polish. add incidental  and billing note.

For all other languages, this customer pays for mileage without pre-approval if the cost is up to $50. If mileage is required above this amount, please contact the account manager for approval. If approved, add incidental (mark billable) and billing note.
main_data.customerSpecialInstructions:
Dear requester,
•if you can initiate a 3 way call on your own, please call the interpreter directly at the time of the appointment
•If you are unable to initiate a 3 way phone call, please call MCIS at 1.888.990.9014 press 0 and ask the coordinator to connect you with the patient and interpreter.

main_data.companySpecialInstructions:
With the onset of the respiratory virus season The Ottawa Hospital has revised its masking requirements. Please note that with immediate effect masking is now a mandatory requirement in all clinical areas and waiting rooms. Clinical areas include inpatient units, nursing stations and ambulatory care areas. In all other areas masking is highly recommended and the hospital encourages everyone to use masks upon entry to the hospital.

Signage will be displayed throughout the hospital sites and masks will be made available.
These requirements will be in place for the duration of the respiratory virus season.
